author: Joe Buczek
title: H.S. boys soccer districts begin
text:
H.S. boys soccer districts begin Posted: 
LUDINGTON – The No. 11-ranked Ludington boys soccer team opened Division 3 district play with an 8-0 shutout over visiting Kingsley on Monday. 
Zach Schoon accounted for six of Ludington’s eight goals in win. 
The Orioles advance to host rival Manistee on Wednesday in a district semifinal. 
In other Division 3 action, Traverse City Christian advanced to a district semifinal with a 6-0 win at Mason County Central. 
The Sabres will face Benzie Central on Wednesday. The Huskies posted a 6-1 victory at Reed City on Monday.
